---
import { Page, Block, Code, info } from '../../components/DocPage.js';
import { Boolean, Event } from '../../components/Links.js';
---

<Page title="event-passive">
  <Block>
    <p>The <strong>event-passive</strong> longhand property specifies if the event should a passive listener.</p>
    <p>event-passive is a longhand version of the <Event /> shorthand's 4th argument. In both forms it accepts a <Boolean /> value.</p>
  </Block>
  <section>
    <h2>Example</h2>
    <Block>
      <p>Specify a listener as <em>passive</em> tells the browser that it will not call <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event/preventDefault">preventDefault</a>. This allows the browser to improve the performance of scrolling, as it knows that scrolling can continue while the event listener is run.</p>
      <Code slot="code" lang="js" code={`
import sheet, { mount } from '${info.cdnURL}';

mount(document, class {
  onscroll() {
    // Browser continues to let user scroll..
  }

  bind() {
    return sheet\`
      body {
        event-listener: scroll \${this.onscroll};
        event-passive: scroll true;
      }
    \`;
  }
});
`} />
    </Block>
  </section>
</Page>